Center: ATOMKI Nuclear Reaction Data Group, Debrecen, Hungary
title: Investigation of the production of the therapeutic radioisotope In-114m through proton and deuteron induced nuclear reactions on cadmium

x4freetext: Investigation of the production of the therapeutic
radioisotope In-114m through proton and deuteron
induced nuclear reactions on cadmium

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4freetext: CGR-560 cyclotron
99.01% enriched Cd-114 electroplated on 12.5 microns
Cu foils, Cd-114 layer thickness 12.8+-1 microns and
12.5 microns natural Cd from Goodfellow were used at
VUB. 97.3% enriched Cd-114 elektroplated on 12.5
microns Al were used in Kharkiv.
Stacked targets containing enriched and natural Cd
foils and Ti, Fe, Cu foils for monitoring and energy
degradation. Irradiation was done in Faraday-cup target
holder with 36, 33 and 16 MeV proton, 21 MeV deuteron
energies at VUB. One stack containing 4 foils was
irradiated with 9.1 MeV incident proton beam in
Kharkiv.
HPGe and Ge(Li) detectors were used. Nuclear data were
taken from NUDAT.
Stopping and energy degradation were calculated using
the Andersen-Ziegler polynomial approximation.
